    <note>Wang(2) Feng [7374] He took the examinations, but did not pass. He established his family [qijia] branch of the lineage when he was placed in charge of the Suzhou prefectural school and then earned the jinshi in 1046. His fifth generation ancestor, Juyan [3946], served in the administration of the Tang dynasty. Feng was Chen(1) Zhiwu's [7125] son-in-law. Feng was the son of Cai(1)  Xiang's [1651] grandniece whose father moved to Suzhou from Xinghua, Putian xian, his first wife was Su(1) Shi. Neither wife produced a son. The Chen(1) woman came from a distinguished family (mingjia). Liu Zai, WJ, 34.13b; Wang Anshi, WJ, 93.965, 100.1033-4 (wife #2, born Chen, who died in 1065 at age of 38). CBD, 1, 171.</note>
